					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-513051#post-1491475</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-513051/scp-1371#post-1491475</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 27 Jun 2012 06:41:17 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Boa Noah</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1340953</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>although it is fairly durable</p> </blockquote> <p>Almost all Axolotls are 'durable', why is this even mentioned? Or can we chuck the thing at walls with little to no damage?</p> <blockquote> <p>SCP-1371 unexpectedly latched onto Researcher Breen's finger, in response Breen grasped SCP-1371 to remove his finger, causing SCP-1371 and Researcher Breen to move 84km into the mesosphere in the space of one hour.</p> </blockquote> <p>Does the guy have horribly degenerated muscles or something? This is a juvenile Axolotl and as such is about as powerful as an infant. So either Breen is incredibly weak and retarded or 1371 is super strong, take your pick.</p> <p>One last quibble:</p> <blockquote> <p>Researcher Sanders attempted to pet SCP-1371</p> </blockquote> <p>Why did he try to pet the airborne larval salamander? I know it looks cute but it's not the kind of critter you physically molest, you give them jumbo earthworms and laugh at their naturally formed grin.</p> <p>All in all either the Foundation doesn't know how to deal with salamanders or the researchers here are poorly chosen for this project.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
